docs.text: snmpbench Benchmark for snmp libraries. The benchmark is focused on how the library perform (Speed, Memory, CPU usage, etc) under different settings (batch size, rounds, sessions, etc). Methodology and source code of the benchmark are located at https://github.com/DataDog/snmpbench Duration per OID Per Batch Size Per Round Per Session Max RSS Per Batch Size Per Round Per Session Elapsed Time Elapsed (wall clock) time Per Batch Size Per Round Per Session Minor Page Faults Minor (reclaiming a frame) page faults Per Batch Size Per Round Per Session System Time Per Batch Size Per Round Per Session User Time Per Batch Size Per Round Per Session Voluntary context switches Per Batch Size Per Round Per Session Involuntary context switches Per Batch Size Per Round Per Session
